T1  - THE POWER OF THE FEDERAL RESERVE CHAIR
AU  - Riboni, Alessandro
AU  - Ruge-Murcia, Francisco
Y1  - 2023/05/01
PY  - 2023
DA  - 2023/05/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12612
T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
JA  - International Economic Review
SP  - 727
EP  - 756
VL  - 64
IS  - 2
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12612
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract This article examines the influence exerted by the Federal Reserve chair on monetary policy decisions. We construct a voting model where the chair selects the proposal that is initially put to a vote but is subject to an acceptance constraint that incorporates the preferences of the median Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) member and the probability of counterproposals. The model is estimated by maximum likelihood using real-time data from FOMC meetings. Results for all chairs in our sample show that the chair's proposal is the result of a compromise, reflecting a stable balance of power within the FOMC.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - DECIDING WHEN TO DECIDE: COLLECTIVE DELIBERATION AND OBSTRUCTION
AU  - Anesi, Vincent
AU  - Safronov, Mikhail
Y1  - 2023/05/01
PY  - 2023
DA  - 2023/05/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12614
T2  - International Economic Review
